  <static seed="2" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/polyMultVar145.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{({a-3b})({a^{2}+7ab+9b^{2}}) = }</m><fillin characters="28" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>a^{3}+4a^{2}b-12ab^{2}-27b^{3}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We multiply the polynomials by using the terms from <m>{a-3b}</m>
successively. <me>\begin{aligned}
        \left({a-3b}\right)\left({a^{2}+7ab+9b^{2}}\right)\amp = {aa^{2}+a\cdot 7ab+a\cdot 9b^{2}-3ba^{2}-3b\cdot 7ab-3b\cdot 9b^{2}}\\
                      \amp  = {a^{3}+4a^{2}b-12ab^{2}-27b^{3}}
    \end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
  </static>
